<div class="container-ex"><div class="row">
  <div class="card-1 col-3">
  <img src="https://www.berlin.de/binaries/asset/image_assets/6773263/source/1626866631/624x468/" alt="alicja kwade">
    <h3>Alicja Kwade: In Abwesenheit</h3>
    <p>18 September 2021 until 4 April 2022</p>
    <p>Alicja Kwade's installations in the exhibition «In Abwesenheit» («In Absence») transform constructions into models for the perception of time, space and matter.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card-2 col-3">
  <img src="https://www.berlin.de/binaries/asset/image_assets/6336564/source/1643010204/624x468/" alt="helmut newton">
    <h3>Helmut Newton. Legacy</h3>
    <p>31 October 2021 until 22 May 2022</p>
    <p>To mark the 100th birthday of the master photographer, the exhibition "Helmut Newton. Legacy" at the Museum of Photography focuses on Newton's fashion photography, including numerous previously unknown or forgotten motifs.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card-3 col-3">
  <img src="https://www.berlin.de/binaries/asset/image_assets/6772792/source/1626767224/624x468/" alt="zanele">
     <h3>Zanele Muholi</h3>
    <p>26 November 2021 until 13 March 2022</p>
    <p>The Gropius Bau in Berlin is dedicating the first retrospective in Germany to the South African activist and photographer Zanele Muholi.</p>
  </div>
